title: Git Cheat Sheet Summary
content: This document is a GitHub Git Cheat Sheet. It lists common Git commands categorized for easy reference, covering Installation & GUIs, Setup, Setup & Init, Stage & Snapshot, Branch & Merge, Inspect & Compare, Share & Update, Tracking Path Changes, Ignoring Patterns, Rewrite History, and Temporary Commits. It provides syntax and descriptions for commands related to repository initialization, configuration, staging, committing, branching, merging, diffing, logging, remote interactions, stashing, and more.

title: TANCET M.C.A. Syllabus
content: The TANCET M.C.A. syllabus includes four main sections: Quantitative ability, Analytical reasoning, Logical reasoning, and Computer awareness. There may also be a few questions on verbal activity and basic science.
